Replace torch.cholesky with torch.linalg.cholesky

Pytorch will deprecate 'torch.cholesky' in the future, so we changed it to
the new api 'torch.linalg.cholesky'.

Return matrix itself when scale() is called

To support using the scaled matrices directly, we have to return the
matrix itself in scale(). Otherwise, it will return "None" which we can
do nothing with it. There is a use case in line 102 of matrices.py.

Fix losing inverse in accumulate_curvature

'update_inv' adds some extra fields(inverse matrices) in the fisher matrix. For
example, KFAC will assign fisher.kron.A_inv with the inverse of A matrix.
Unfortunately, 'accumulate_curvature' uses SymMatrix.__add__  which creating a
new one that omits these extra fields. That means we lose the inverse matrices.
Now we fixed it by using SymMatrix.__iadd__ which can keep them safe.
